{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"LC84ewt3lQFZfwH5x6URzlFZAdg=","kind":"plan","title":"Slice 3 — Provenance + Path Addressing Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"NR5f8qjCEoUVfyHDuNopYpUpSSI=","body":"# Slice 3 — Provenance + Path Addressing Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Record an append-only **origin log** on each entry (who/what, from where, how, when) and let `show`/`restore` address an entry by a file path via its kref-id trailer.\n\n**Architecture:** A new append-only `RecordOrigin` operation on the git-bug `entity/dag` (appended to the op-type iota); `Snapshot.Provenance []OriginEvent`. `add` records a `create` event; `ingest` records an `ingest` event (only when it created/updated) carrying a **repo-root-relative** source path. The actor is the git identity (`human`) unless `--actor`/`KREF_ACTOR` marks it an `agent`. Path addressing reuses the existing kref-id trailer (`bridge` exposes `IDFromFile`). All logic in `internal/store`/`internal/entry`/`internal/bridge`; commands stay thin.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go 1.26.4, cobra, ginkgo/gomega, git-bug `entity/dag`. No new dependencies.\n\n**Spec:** `docs/dev/specs/2026-06-20-unified-entry-model-design.md` §4.3, with these locked refinements:\n- OriginEvent = `{ actor, actor_kind, source_path, trigger, time }`. `originRepo` is **deferred**.\n- Actor: `--actor \u003cname\u003e` flag or `KREF_ACTOR` env ⇒ `actor_kind=agent`, `actor=\u003cname\u003e`; absent ⇒ `actor_kind=human`, `actor=`git identity name. (Self-asserted, like the git author — a context/trust signal, not authorization.)\n- `source_path` is **repo-root-relative** (basename if the file is outside the repo); never absolute.\n- `ingest` records an event only on `created`/`updated` (not `unchanged`/`error`).\n\n## Critical compatibility note\n\nNew op types MUST be **appended** to the END of the `OperationType` iota (after `RemoveLabelOp`) — the numeric type is serialized; inserting mid-iota corrupts existing entries.\n\n## File Structure\n\n- **Modify** `internal/entry/operations.go` — `RecordOriginOp` (appended), `RecordOrigin` op, unmarshaler case.\n- **Modify** `internal/entry/snapshot.go` — `OriginEvent` type + `Provenance []OriginEvent`.\n- **Modify** `internal/entry/operations_test.go` — RecordOrigin Apply test.\n- **Modify** `internal/store/store.go` — `RecordOrigin` method; `RepoRelative(path)` helper.\n- **Modify** `internal/store/store_test.go` — store provenance + RepoRelative tests.\n- **Modify** `internal/bridge/bridge.go` — `IDFromFile(path)`; thread actor into `Ingest`/`IngestPaths`; record ingest origin.\n- **Modify** `internal/bridge/bridge_test.go` — IDFromFile test.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/main.go` — `--actor` persistent flag.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/commands.go` — `resolveActor`; `add` records create-origin; `ingest` passes actor; `show`/`restore` accept a path arg.\n- **Modify** `internal/render/render.go` + `render_test.go` — provenance in `show`.\n- **Modify** `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` — CLI specs.\n- **Modify** `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`.\n\nSequencing: op/snapshot (T1) → store method + path helper (T2) → actor + `add` (T3) → `ingest` (T4) → render (T5) → path addressing (T6) → docs/verify (T7).\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: `RecordOrigin` op + `OriginEvent` + `Snapshot.Provenance`\n\n**Files:** `internal/entry/operations.go`, `internal/entry/snapshot.go`, `internal/entry/operations_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Add `OriginEvent` + `Provenance` to the snapshot**\n\nIn `internal/entry/snapshot.go`, add an `OriginEvent` type (place it next to the `Link` type) :\n\n```go\n// OriginEvent is one entry in an entry's append-only provenance log.\ntype OriginEvent struct {\n\tActor      string    `json:\"actor\"`\n\tActorKind  string    `json:\"actor_kind\"` // human | agent\n\tSourcePath string    `json:\"source_path\"`\n\tTrigger    string    `json:\"trigger\"` // create | ingest\n\tTime       time.Time `json:\"time\"`\n}\n```\n\nand add to the `Snapshot` struct, after `Labels []string`:\n\n```go\n\tProvenance     []OriginEvent `json:\"provenance\"`\n```\n\n(`snapshot.go` already imports `\"time\"`.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the failing Apply test**\n\nAppend to `internal/entry/operations_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"RecordOrigin\", func() {\n\tIt(\"appends an origin event (append-only, in order)\", func() {\n\t\tauthor := newAuthor(newTestRepo())\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{}\n\t\tentry.NewRecordOrigin(author, \"alice\", \"human\", \"\", \"create\").Apply(s)\n\t\tentry.NewRecordOrigin(author, \"claude\", \"agent\", \"docs/n.md\", \"ingest\").Apply(s)\n\t\tExpect(s.Provenance).To(HaveLen(2))\n\t\tExpect(s.Provenance[0].Trigger).To(Equal(\"create\"))\n\t\tExpect(s.Provenance[1].Actor).To(Equal(\"claude\"))\n\t\tExpect(s.Provenance[1].ActorKind).To(Equal(\"agent\"))\n\t\tExpect(s.Provenance[1].SourcePath).To(Equal(\"docs/n.md\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"validates a non-empty trigger\", func() {\n\t\tauthor := newAuthor(newTestRepo())\n\t\tExpect(entry.NewRecordOrigin(author, \"a\", \"human\", \"\", \"\").Validate()).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(entry.NewRecordOrigin(author, \"a\", \"human\", \"\", \"create\").Validate()).To(Succeed())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run the test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -6`\nExpected: FAIL — `undefined: entry.NewRecordOrigin`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Append the op type to the iota**\n\nIn `internal/entry/operations.go`, the `OperationType` iota currently ends with `AddLabelOp`, `RemoveLabelOp`. Append at the end:\n\n```go\n\tRemoveLabelOp\n\tRecordOriginOp\n)\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Implement the op**\n\nAppend to `internal/entry/operations.go` (it already imports `time`, `fmt`, `dag`, `entity`, `identity`):\n\n```go\n// RecordOrigin appends a provenance event. The log is append-only.\ntype RecordOrigin struct {\n\tdag.OpBase\n\tActor      string `json:\"actor\"`\n\tActorKind  string `json:\"actor_kind\"`\n\tSourcePath string `json:\"source_path\"`\n\tTrigger    string `json:\"trigger\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewRecordOrigin(author identity.Interface, actor, actorKind, sourcePath, trigger string) *RecordOrigin {\n\treturn \u0026RecordOrigin{\n\t\tOpBase:     dag.NewOpBase(RecordOriginOp, author, time.Now().Unix()),\n\t\tActor:      actor,\n\t\tActorKind:  actorKind,\n\t\tSourcePath: sourcePath,\n\t\tTrigger:    trigger,\n\t}\n}\nfunc (op *RecordOrigin) Id() entity.Id { return dag.IdOperation(op, \u0026op.OpBase) }\nfunc (op *RecordOrigin) Validate() error {\n\tif op.Trigger == \"\" {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"origin trigger required\")\n\t}\n\treturn op.OpBase.Validate(op, RecordOriginOp)\n}\nfunc (op *RecordOrigin) Apply(s *Snapshot) {\n\ts.Provenance = append(s.Provenance, OriginEvent{\n\t\tActor:      op.Actor,\n\t\tActorKind:  op.ActorKind,\n\t\tSourcePath: op.SourcePath,\n\t\tTrigger:    op.Trigger,\n\t\tTime:       op.Time(),\n\t})\n\ts.UpdatedAt = op.Time()\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Register in the unmarshaler**\n\nIn `operationUnmarshaler`, add before `default:`:\n\n```go\n\tcase RecordOriginOp:\n\t\top = \u0026RecordOrigin{}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Run the test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/entry/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS. Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./internal/entry/`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/entry/operations.go internal/entry/snapshot.go internal/entry/operations_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(entry): RecordOrigin op + Snapshot.Provenance (append-only log)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: `store.RecordOrigin` + repo-relative path helper\n\n**Files:** `internal/store/store.go`, `internal/store/store_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing store tests**\n\nAppend to `internal/store/store_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"Store provenance\", func() {\n\tIt(\"records an origin event on an entry\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"Tester\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"T\", \"b\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n\t\tExpect(s.RecordOrigin(id, \"claude\", \"agent\", \"docs/n.md\", \"ingest\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(snap.Provenance).To(HaveLen(1))\n\t\tExpect(snap.Provenance[0].SourcePath).To(Equal(\"docs/n.md\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"normalizes a path to repo-root-relative, basename if outside\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"Tester\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\t// Inside the repo → relative to root.\n\t\tExpect(s.RepoRelative(filepath.Join(dir, \"docs\", \"n.md\"))).To(Equal(\"docs/n.md\"))\n\t\t// Outside the repo → basename only (no leak of absolute structure).\n\t\tExpect(s.RepoRelative(\"/etc/secret/notes.md\")).To(Equal(\"notes.md\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\nEnsure `store_test.go` imports `\"path/filepath\"` (add if missing).\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the store tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -6`\nExpected: FAIL — `s.RecordOrigin undefined`, `s.RepoRelative undefined`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement `RecordOrigin` (mirror `SetStatus`)**\n\nAdd to `internal/store/store.go`:\n\n```go\n// RecordOrigin appends a provenance event to an entry, searching all tiers.\nfunc (s *Store) RecordOrigin(id entity.Id, actor, actorKind, sourcePath, trigger string) error {\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\te, err := entry.Read(s.repo, t, id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tif entity.IsErrNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"read %s in tier %s: %w\", id, t, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewRecordOrigin(s.author, actor, actorKind, sourcePath, trigger))\n\t\treturn e.Commit(s.repo)\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s not found\", id)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Implement `RepoRelative`**\n\nThe `Store` has a `dir` field (the directory it was opened against). Add a helper that resolves the repo root by walking up to `.git`, then makes `path` relative to it; if `path` is outside the repo, return its basename. Add `\"os\"` to `store.go`'s import block (`\"path/filepath\"` and `\"strings\"` are already imported; `\"os\"` is not — only `\"os/exec\"` is).\n\n```go\n// RepoRelative renders path relative to the repository root. A path outside the\n// repo collapses to its basename so an absolute local path never leaks into the\n// (syncable) provenance log.\nfunc (s *Store) RepoRelative(path string) string {\n\troot := repoRoot(s.dir)\n\tabs, err := filepath.Abs(path)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn filepath.Base(path)\n\t}\n\trel, err := filepath.Rel(root, abs)\n\tif err != nil || rel == \"..\" || strings.HasPrefix(rel, \"..\"+string(filepath.Separator)) {\n\t\treturn filepath.Base(path)\n\t}\n\treturn filepath.ToSlash(rel)\n}\n\n// repoRoot walks up from start to the directory containing .git; falls back to\n// the absolute form of start if none is found.\nfunc repoRoot(start string) string {\n\tdir, err := filepath.Abs(start)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn start\n\t}\n\tfor {\n\t\tif _, err := os.Stat(filepath.Join(dir, \".git\")); err == nil {\n\t\t\treturn dir\n\t\t}\n\t\tparent := filepath.Dir(dir)\n\t\tif parent == dir {\n\t\t\treturn dir\n\t\t}\n\t\tdir = parent\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n(`store.go` already imports `\"strings\"` from slice 1.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the store tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -5`\nExpected: PASS. Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./internal/store/`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/store/store.go internal/store/store_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(store): RecordOrigin + RepoRelative (repo-root-relative, basename fallback)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: `--actor` resolution + `add` records a create-origin\n\n**Files:** `cmd/kref/main.go`, `cmd/kref/commands.go`, `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing CLI spec**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"add provenance\", func() {\n\tIt(\"records a human create-origin by default\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"Alice\", \"--email\", \"a@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--title\", \"X\", \"--body\", \"b\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar a struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026a)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tshown := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", a.ID, \"--json\")\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(`\"trigger\": \"create\"`))\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(`\"actor_kind\": \"human\"`))\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(`\"actor\": \"Alice\"`))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"records an agent create-origin when --actor is set\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"Alice\", \"--email\", \"a@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--actor\", \"claude\", \"--title\", \"Y\", \"--body\", \"b\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar a struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026a)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tshown := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", a.ID, \"--json\")\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(`\"actor_kind\": \"agent\"`))\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(`\"actor\": \"claude\"`))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the spec to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — no provenance recorded (and `unknown flag: --actor`).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add the `--actor` persistent flag**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/main.go`, after the `--json` persistent flag registration, add:\n\n```go\n\troot.PersistentFlags().String(\"actor\", \"\", \"attribute actions to an agent (else the git identity, as human)\")\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Add `resolveActor` and call it from `add`**\n\nAdd to `cmd/kref/commands.go` (it imports `os`):\n\n```go\n// resolveActor returns (actor, actorKind). --actor flag or KREF_ACTOR env marks an\n// agent; otherwise the git identity name as a human.\nfunc resolveActor(cmd *cobra.Command, s *store.Store) (string, string) {\n\tv, _ := cmd.Flags().GetString(\"actor\")\n\tif v == \"\" {\n\t\tv = os.Getenv(\"KREF_ACTOR\")\n\t}\n\tif v != \"\" {\n\t\treturn v, \"agent\"\n\t}\n\tname, _ := s.Author()\n\treturn name, \"human\"\n}\n```\n\nIn `newAddCmd`, after the label loop and BEFORE `snap, err := s.Get(id)`, add:\n\n```go\n\t\t\tactor, actorKind := resolveActor(cmd, s)\n\t\t\tif err := s.RecordOrigin(id, actor, actorKind, \"\", \"create\"); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the suite to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: PASS. Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./cmd/kref/`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add cmd/kref/main.go cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(provenance): --actor resolution; add records a create-origin\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: `ingest` records an ingest-origin with the source path\n\n**Files:** `internal/bridge/bridge.go`, `cmd/kref/commands.go`, `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing CLI spec**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"ingest provenance\", func() {\n\tIt(\"records an ingest-origin with the repo-relative source path\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(os.MkdirAll(filepath.Join(dir, \"docs\"), 0o755)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tmd := filepath.Join(dir, \"docs\", \"note.md\")\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(md, []byte(\"# Note\\n\\nbody\\n\"), 0o644)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"ingest\", md, \"--json\")\n\t\tvar arr []map[string]any\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026arr)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tid := arr[0][\"id\"].(string)\n\n\t\tshown := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", id, \"--json\")\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(`\"trigger\": \"ingest\"`))\n\t\tExpect(shown).To(ContainSubstring(`\"source_path\": \"docs/note.md\"`))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the spec to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — no ingest provenance.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Thread actor through `bridge.Ingest`/`IngestPaths` and record the origin**\n\nIn `internal/bridge/bridge.go`, change the two signatures and record the origin whenever an entry was created or genuinely updated (never on `unchanged`/error). Update `Ingest`:\n\n```go\nfunc Ingest(s *store.Store, path string, tier entry.Tier, actor, actorKind string) (IngestResult, error) {\n```\n\nThere are two success return sites. Insert the `RecordOrigin` call distinctly at each (the `action` value differs):\n\n1. **Update path** — the return `return IngestResult{Path: path, ID: id, Title: title, Tier: existing.Tier, Action: action}, nil`. Insert immediately before it, guarded so a no-op re-ingest records nothing:\n```go\n\t\t\tif action == \"updated\" {\n\t\t\t\tif err := s.RecordOrigin(id, actor, actorKind, s.RepoRelative(path), \"ingest\"); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn IngestResult{}, err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n```\n\n2. **Create path** — the return `return IngestResult{Path: path, ID: id, Title: title, Tier: string(tier), Quarantined: secret, Action: action}, nil`. A create is always a real write (`action` is `created` or `quarantined`), so record unconditionally. Insert immediately before that return:\n```go\n\tif err := s.RecordOrigin(id, actor, actorKind, s.RepoRelative(path), \"ingest\"); err != nil {\n\t\treturn IngestResult{}, err\n\t}\n```\n\nUpdate `IngestPaths` to take and forward the actor:\n\n```go\nfunc IngestPaths(s *store.Store, paths []string, tier entry.Tier, skipMissing bool, actor, actorKind string) ([]IngestResult, error) {\n```\n\nand change its internal call `Ingest(s, f, tier)` to `Ingest(s, f, tier, actor, actorKind)`.\n\n**Update the existing bridge tests** (`internal/bridge/bridge_test.go`, package `bridge`): there are 8 direct `Ingest(s, …, entry.Tier…)` calls and 2 `IngestPaths(s, …)` calls. Append `, \"tester\", \"human\"` to each so they match the new signatures.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Pass the actor from the ingest command**\n\nIn `cmd/kref/commands.go` `newIngestCmd`, resolve the actor after opening the store and pass it to `IngestPaths`. Replace `results, err := bridge.IngestPaths(s, args, t, skipMissing)` with:\n\n```go\n\t\t\tactor, actorKind := resolveActor(cmd, s)\n\t\t\tresults, err := bridge.IngestPaths(s, args, t, skipMissing, actor, actorKind)\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the suite to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ ./internal/bridge/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: PASS (the existing bridge tests that call `Ingest`/`IngestPaths` directly must be updated to pass the two new args — if any fail to compile, update those call sites to pass `\"tester\", \"human\"`). Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./internal/bridge/ ./cmd/kref/`.\n\n\u003e If `internal/bridge/bridge_test.go` calls `Ingest`/`IngestPaths` directly, add `\"tester\", \"human\"` as the trailing args at each call site.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/bridge/bridge.go cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go internal/bridge/bridge_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(provenance): ingest records an ingest-origin with the repo-relative path\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: Render provenance in `show`\n\n**Files:** `internal/render/render.go`, `internal/render/render_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing render test**\n\nAppend to `internal/render/render_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"provenance rendering\", func() {\n\tIt(\"renders an Origin line per event in show\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{\n\t\t\tID: entity.Id(\"a\"), Tier: \"shared\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"T\",\n\t\t\tProvenance: []entry.OriginEvent{\n\t\t\t\t{Actor: \"claude\", ActorKind: \"agent\", SourcePath: \"docs/n.md\", Trigger: \"ingest\"},\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t}\n\t\trender.Show(\u0026b, s, false)\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"Origin: ingest by claude (agent)\"))\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).To(ContainSubstring(\"docs/n.md\"))\n\t})\n\tIt(\"omits origin lines when there is no provenance\", func() {\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\ts := \u0026entry.Snapshot{ID: entity.Id(\"a\"), Tier: \"shared\", Status: \"open\", Title: \"T\"}\n\t\trender.Show(\u0026b, s, false)\n\t\tExpect(b.String()).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"Origin:\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the render test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -8`\nExpected: FAIL — no Origin line.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Render provenance in `Show`**\n\nIn `internal/render/render.go` `Show`, after the existing labels block (`if len(snap.Labels) \u003e 0 { ... }`) and BEFORE the final `fmt.Fprintf(w, \"\\n%s\\n\", snap.Body)`, add:\n\n```go\n\tfor _, o := range snap.Provenance {\n\t\tline := fmt.Sprintf(\"Origin: %s by %s (%s)\", o.Trigger, o.Actor, o.ActorKind)\n\t\tif o.SourcePath != \"\" {\n\t\t\tline += \" from \" + o.SourcePath\n\t\t}\n\t\tfmt.Fprintln(w, line)\n\t}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run the render test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/render/ ./cmd/kref/ 2\u003e\u00261 | tail -6`\nExpected: PASS. Run `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go vet ./internal/render/`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/render/render.go internal/render/render_test.go\ngit commit